EXAMPLE

<example><statement>
    <p>Find the sine of the labeled angle in each triangle below. </p> <sidebyside widths="45% 40%"><image source="images/exam2-2-1a.png"><description>triangle</description></image><image source="images/exam2-2-1b.png"><description>triangle</description></image></sidebyside></statement>
<solution>
    <p><ol label="a">
        <li><p>The side opposite angle <m>\phi</m> is 5, and the hypotenuse is 13, so the sine of <m>\phi</m> is <me>\text{sin } \phi =\dfrac{5}{13}, \text{  or approximately}~~ 0.3846</me> </p></li>
        <li><p>The side opposite angle <m>\beta</m> is <m>\sqrt{5}</m>, and the hypotenuse is 3, so the sine of <m>\beta</m> is <me>\text{sin } \beta =\dfrac{\sqrt{5}}{3}, \text{  or approximately}~~ 0.7454</me></p></li>
    </ol></p></solution>
</example>

